  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "*Title*: Envoy does not build behind a proxy\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nNormally when behind a proxy one can specify proxy environment (`HTTP_PROXY`, `https_proxy`, etc.) variables which tells git and other tools to use a proxy when making outbound http/-s requests. However, due to parts of the envoy build chain ignoring these settings bazel is unable to pull down external repositories. \r\n\r\nExample of what it looks like:\r\n```\r\n ERROR: /home/snowp/.cache/bazel/_bazel_snowp/c3ec2354b418a2642552c8e873fd0f54/external/com_lyft_protoc_gen_validate/validate/BUILD:35:1: no such package '@com_github_golang_protobuf//proto': failed to fetch com_github_golang_protobuf: # cd .; git clone https://github.com/golang/protobuf /home/snowp/.cache/bazel/_bazel_snowp/c3ec2354b418a2642552c8e873fd0f54/external/com_github_golang_protobuf\r\nCloning into '/home/snowp/.cache/bazel/_bazel_snowp/c3ec2354b418a2642552c8e873fd0f54/external/com_github_golang_protobuf'...\r\nfatal: unable to access 'https://github.com/golang/protobuf/': Failed connect to github.com:443; Operation now in progress\r\n2018/02/11 04:40:35 exit status 128\r\n and referenced by '@com_lyft_protoc_gen_validate//validate:go_default_library'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe fix involves updating `io_bazel_rules_go` to a newer version (we need [this](https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_go/commit/812c172b921cafaa27a58bba2d2cd37ace296b88)) + ensuring that all dependencies use the Skylark `git_repository` instead of the native `git_repository` (see [here](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/3893)). \r\n\r\nI've already started working on this (see https://github.com/lyft/protoc-gen-validate/pull/57 + https://github.com/lyft/protoc-gen-validate/pull/59), so I'm mainly filing this for informational + tracking purposes. Feel free to assign me to this issue. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
